snippet: Investigators are questioning the family and friends of Hassan Abdi Dhuhulow, a Norwegian citizen born in Somalia, whose sister said he began taking “long vacations” there in 2009.
abstract: Norwegian investigators are questioning family and friends of Somali immigrant Hassan Abdi Dhuhulow, who grew up in Norway, in effort to determine whether he was one of four attackers caught on surveillance cameras during rampage at Westgate shopping mall in Nairobi, Kenya

byline.original: By HENRIK PRYSER LIBELL and NICHOLAS KULISH
byline.contributor: Henrik Pryser Libell reported from Larvik, and Nicholas Kulish from Nairobi, Kenya. Josh Kron contributed reporting from Nairobi.

lead_paragraph: Investigators are questioning the family and friends of Hassan Abdi Dhuhulow, a Norwegian citizen born in Somalia, whose sister said he began taking “long vacations” there in 2009.

headline.main: In Kenya Inquiry, Norway Looks at Somali Migrant
headline.print_headline: In Kenya Inquiry, Norway Looks at Somali Migrant
